  "prompt": "I'm a rookie. How should I start preparing for getting selected in GSoC 17?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to help you prepare for Google Summer of Code (GSoC) 2017:\n\n1. Choose Your Skills and Focus\n- Identify your programming language strengths\n- Determine which technologies you're most comfortable with\n- Select open-source organizations aligned with your skills\n\n2. Technical Preparation\n- Improve coding skills\n- Learn version control (Git)\n- Practice contributing to open-source projects\n- Understand GitHub workflow\n- Build a strong GitHub profile with personal projects\n\n3. Research Organizations\n- Browse GSoC website\n- Review previous years' organizations\n- Look at accepted project ideas\n- Check organization repositories\n- Understand their coding standards\n\n4. Start Contributing Early\n- Make small contributions to potential organizations\n- Fix bugs\n- Improve documentation\n- Participate in mailing lists\n- Engage with community members\n\n5. Proposal Preparation\n- Understand project requirements thoroughly\n- Draft a detailed, clear proposal\n- Outline project milestones\n- Demonstrate technical feasibility\n- Show understanding of organization's goals\n\n6. Communication\n- Be active on organization's communication channels\n- Ask intelligent questions\n- Show genuine interest\n- Network with mentors and community members\n\n7. Technical Skills\n- Learn relevant programming languages\n- Study algorithms and data structures\n- Practice coding challenges\n- Build small projects\n\n8. Seek Guidance\n- Connect with previous GSoC participants\n- Attend local developer meetups\n- Join online forums\n- Get feedback on your proposal\n\n9. Timeline Management\n- Start early (December-January)\n- Set personal deadlines\n- Practice consistent coding\n- Be patient and persistent\n\n10. Backup Plan\n- Apply to multiple organizations\n- Have alternative project ideas\n- Don't get discouraged by rejections\n\nAdditional Tips:\n- Keep learning\n- Stay motivated\n- Be proactive\n- Showcase your passion\n\nGood luck with your GSoC journey!",
